               <p>The prisoner lived <rs id="t17630914-84-deflabel457" type="occupation">servant</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17630914-84-defend670 t17630914-84-deflabel457"></join> with Mr. Hagard, next door to Mr. Hamilton's, in Chancery-lane; a quantity of numbers of Smollet's History of England being sold by the prisoner to Mr. Showel, a cheesemonger, in Fleet-market, he serving Mr. Hamilton with butter, &amp;c. some of the said paper was sent there with goods, by which means it came out; the numbers were looked over in Mr. Hamilton's warehouse, and the quantity mentioned in the indictment missing.</p>
               <p>Mr. Showel deposed, that the prisoner brought and sold it him as waste paper.</p>
